The Delta State Police Command has arrested a 27-year-old suspect, Chukwudi Emerenin, for allegedly killing a retired policeman. The retired officer in charge of legal department, Christ Kpatuma, was reportedly killed in Agwa Clan, Oguta Local Government Area of Imo State. The Commissioner of Police, Delta State Command, Muhammed Ali, while parading the suspect on Wednesday along with 39 others at the police headquarters, Asaba, said that the suspect was part of the syndicate that killed the late police officer. He said, “Last week, unknown gunmen killed a retired police officer, our O/C Legal who hailed from Imo State. “He served here in Delta State and retired meritoriously and the police took it as a point of duty to fish out the killers. The command has made a breakthrough and arrested the suspect. “The suspect was arrested by operatives of the command while acting on intelligence gathered that he and his gang members were hibernating somewhere in Aboh in Ndokwa East Area of Delta State.” Ali disclosed that the suspect is an escapee from Owerri prison, urging parents and guardians to monitor and caution their children against criminality. He said he had directed all Divisional Police Officers and Area Commanders to continue raiding criminal hideouts. Others paraded included suspected kidnappers, armed robbers, 11 suspected cultists, murder suspects, and suspected drug barons among others.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com